---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SOCIAL } from '../consts';
import { buildPersonJsonLd } from '../lib/jsonld';

const personJsonLd = buildPersonJsonLd(new URL('/about/', Astro.site).toString());
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <BaseHead
      title="About — Marcos Augusto"
      description="A bit more about who I am and what I'm working on."
      jsonLd={personJsonLd}
      alternateLocales={[{ locale: 'pt', url: '/pt/about/' }]}
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <Header />
    <main class="site-container page-main">
      <article class="prose prose-column">
        <h1>About</h1>

        <p class="lead">
          I'm Marcos Augusto, a software engineer based in Brazil. I work at
          <a href="https://nubank.com.br">Nubank</a> as a mobile engineer, building in Flutter on the
          platform layer of an app that serves tens of millions of customers. Before mobile I spent
          years in frontend — and a stretch in Clojure on large backend systems — which is why I care
          equally about how things look and whether they
          survive production.
        </p>

        <p>
          By night and weekend I build small things — finance trackers, expense readers, sim-racing
          telemetry dashboards, home tooling — and increasingly, agent infrastructure on top of
          <a href="https://opencode.ai">opencode</a> and Claude Code, including
          <a href="https://github.com/maugustosemperfi/cli-dm">cli-dm</a>, a public tracker that turns
          Claude Code sessions into a map of agents, tasks, and milestones.
        </p>

        <p>
          Not all meaningful work fits a public GitHub profile. Some products are live while their
          source stays private — Fatura Reader is one — and my day job ships inside a private monorepo.
          I write about the problems, product decisions, and engineering tradeoffs instead of linking to
          code.
        </p>

        <h2>The story so far</h2>
        <ol class="timeline" data-timeline>
          <li class="timeline-era reveal-era">
            <span class="timeline-period">7</span>
            <h3>Frontend years.</h3>
            <p>
              Building for the web at MV, Loft and others. Where the UI taste comes from.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="timeline-era reveal-era">
            <span class="timeline-period">3 →</span>
            <h3>Nubank — Flutter and Clojure.</h3>
            <p>
              Not a handoff from backend to mobile — both at once. Clojure on large systems that
              serve tens of millions of customers; Flutter on the mobile platform — design system,
              internationalization, release tooling — the layer other engineers build on.
            </p>
          </li>
          <li class="timeline-era reveal-era">
            <span class="timeline-period">2025 →</span>
            <h3>The agents thread.</h3>
            <p>
              Skills, harnesses, orchestration — running alongside everything else.
            </p>
          </li>
        </ol>

        <h2>What this blog is</h2>
        <p>
          A place to write down what I learn while doing the work. Not tutorials, not announcements —
          more like a public lab notebook.
        </p>

        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Mobile and design systems.</strong> Flutter at scale, design tokens, i18n, release
            engineering — written generically, no employer internals.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Agent skills, harnesses, orchestration.</strong> I use and curate a mixed set of
            agent workflows, some mine and some borrowed. I also build tools like <code>cli-dm</code>
            to make agent work visible as it unfolds. I'll write about what holds up, what falls apart,
            and what is worth making your own.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Personal tools.</strong> The small fintech and tracker apps I build for myself —
            including some private repositories — and the design decisions behind them.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Sim racing.</strong> iRacing + SimHub dashboards, telemetry, and the weird
            native-code edges that come with it.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>Plus the occasional war story from the Clojure years.</p>

        <h2>Stack I reach for</h2>
        <p>
          Flutter / Dart, TypeScript, React, Next.js, Clojure, Python, Postgres. Whatever the problem
          actually wants.
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          Easiest is <a href={SOCIAL.twitter}>X / Twitter</a> or
          <a href={SOCIAL.email}>email</a>. Code on
          <a href={SOCIAL.github}>GitHub</a>.
          {SOCIAL.linkedin && (
            <>
              {' '}Profile on <a href={SOCIAL.linkedin}>LinkedIn</a>.
            </>
          )}
        </p>
      </article>
    </main>
    <Footer />

    <script>
      const eras = document.querySelectorAll('.reveal-era');
      const reduced = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;

      if (reduced) {
        eras.forEach((era) => era.classList.add('is-visible'));
      } else if ('IntersectionObserver' in window) {
        const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
          (entries) => {
            entries.forEach((entry) => {
              if (entry.isIntersecting) {
                entry.target.classList.add('is-visible');
                observer.unobserve(entry.target);
              }
            });
          },
          { threshold: 0.2 },
        );
        eras.forEach((era) => observer.observe(era));
      } else {
        eras.forEach((era) => era.classList.add('is-visible'));
      }
    </script>

    <style>
      .page-main {
        padding-block: var(--space-8) var(--space-24);
      }

      .prose h1 {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-8);
      }

      .prose h2 {
        margin-top: var(--space-12);
        margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
      }

      .prose p {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-4);
      }

      .prose ul,
      .prose ol {
        margin-bottom: var(--space-6);
      }

      .lead {
        font-size: var(--text-lg);
        line-height: var(--leading-snug);
        color: var(--color-text);
      }

      .lead a {
        font-weight: 500;
      }

      .timeline {
        position: relative;
        list-style: none;
        margin: var(--space-8) 0 var(--space-12);
        padding: 0 0 0 var(--space-8);
      }

      .timeline::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        left: 0.45rem;
        top: 0.5rem;
        bottom: 0.5rem;
        width: 2px;
        background: var(--color-border-strong);
      }

      .timeline-era {
        position: relative;
        padding: 0 0 var(--space-8) var(--space-8);
        opacity: 0;
        transform: translateX(-12px);
        transition:
          opacity 500ms var(--ease-out-quint),
          transform 500ms var(--ease-out-quint);
      }

      .timeline-era.is-visible {
        opacity: 1;
        transform: translateX(0);
      }

      .timeline-era::before {
        content: '';
        position: absolute;
        left: calc(-1 * var(--space-8) + 0.15rem);
        top: 0.45rem;
        width: 12px;
        height: 12px;
        border: 2px solid var(--color-rust);
        border-radius: 999px;
        background: var(--color-bg);
      }

      .timeline-period {
        display: block;
        margin-bottom: var(--space-2);
        color: var(--color-rust);
        font-family: var(--font-mono);
        font-size: var(--text-xs);
        font-weight: 500;
        font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums;
        letter-spacing: 0.02em;
      }

      .timeline-era h3 {
        margin: 0 0 var(--space-2);
        font-family: var(--font-heading);
        font-size: var(--text-xl);
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      .timeline-era p {
        margin: 0;
        color: var(--color-text-secondary);
        font-size: var(--text-sm);
        line-height: 1.6;
      }

      @media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
        .timeline-era {
          opacity: 1;
          transform: none;
          transition: none;
        }
      }
    </style>
  </body>
</html>
